	<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">With the limitted amount of 'damage' being done=2E=2E=2E ie: "deleting=
 characters" and "taking over characters" it sounds like the=
 'parties' have not really tapped into the full database,=
 possibly, and there is no note of them making themselves or=
 others uber1337=2E=2E=2E

A few scenarios I can think of right off hand=2E=2E=2E
in no paticular order=2E=2E=2E

First,=2E=2E=2E it is a software hole in the game itself which allows=
 for them to sniff others authorizations, and or reset anothers=
 password to then take control

Second,=2E=2E=2E Social Engineering e-mails or forum posts or chat=
 entries used to harvest anothers account settings=2E=2E=2E 

third=2E=2E=2E  Third party applications meant to make a user uber1337=
 but in fact is a sort of 'trojan' and reports back user infos to=
 the creator(s)=2E=2E

the latter two would not really be the responsibility of the MMM=
 obviously=2E=2E=2E  


Just some obvious scenarios that stick out to me=2E=2E=2E 

